      "content": "I would advise against overusing ibuprofen, as it's not a suitable long-term solution for managing chronic pain. Taking one 400mg tablet every 2 hours may lead to rebound headaches and stomach problems. Instead, consider taking a full dose of ibuprofen every 4-6 hours, as directed on the label. Additionally, you may want to try applying heat or cold packs to your lower back, or stretching gently to loosen up tight muscles.",
